SIMPLE: shibboleth
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shibboleth
<hw>Shib"bo*leth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb.
<ets>shibb⟦omac⟧leth</ets> an ear of corn, or a stream, a flood.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A word which was made the criterion by which to
distinguish the Ephraimites from the Gileadites. The Ephraimites, not
being able to pronounce <xex>sh</xex>, called the word
<xex>sibboleth</xex>. See <au>Judges xii.</au></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Without reprieve, adjudged to death,⟦br⟧
For want of well pronouncing <qex>shibboleth</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><def>Also used in an extended sense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>th</qex>, with its twofold value, is . . . the
<qex>shibboleth</qex> of foreigners.</q> <rj><qau>Earle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, the criterion, test, or watchword of a party;
a party cry or pet phrase.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shicer</ent>⟦br⟧
